senses.sense_definition: A surname of Old French origin.

examples.text: Mr. <w>Burrell</w> has been managing the estate for over twenty years.
She was surprised to find another <w>Burrell</w> living in the same small village.

senses.sense_definition: A place name used for various locations in the United States, including townships in Pennsylvania and Iowa.

examples.text: The small community of <w>Burrell</w> is located in a rural part of the county.
They looked at the map to find the boundaries of <w>Burrell</w> Township.
